🌟 GlowField

GlowField is a server-side Fabric mod that creates dynamic, configurable force-field zones using Respawn Anchors. These zones protect areas by preventing mob spawns, damaging hostile entities, and rendering a visible particle-based barrier—all without requiring any client-side mods.

⸻

⚡ Features

🛡️ Force Field Zones
	•	Create protected areas using 4 Respawn Anchors
	•	Forms a rectangular 3D zone from world bottom to top
	•	Fully server-side — vanilla clients can join without installing anything

⸻

🔋 Charge-Based Behavior

Zones automatically change behavior based on anchor charge levels:
	•	All anchors fully charged (4 charges)
→ Force Field Mode
	•	Damages mobs that enter
	•	Strong visual particle barrier
	•	All anchors have ≥1 charge
→ Spawn Prevention Mode
	•	Prevents hostile mob spawning
	•	Softer visual effect
	•	Any anchor uncharged
→ Inactive
	•	Zone does nothing

⸻

⚠️ Degradation System

Force fields are not infinite:
	•	Every N mobs prevented or damaged (configurable)
→ reduces anchor charge by 1
	•	Encourages maintenance and recharging

⸻

✨ Particle Force Field
	•	Full 3D perimeter rendering
	•	Configurable particle types per state:
	•	Force Field → e.g. portal
	•	Spawn Prevention → e.g. smoke
	•	Inactive → e.g. end rod
	•	Rendered server-side via packets

⸻

🧠 Smart Performance Design
	•	Chunk-indexed zones (no global scanning)
	•	Event-driven updates (no ticking loops)
	•	Efficient entity queries via bounding boxes
	•	Scales to many zones without lag

⸻

💾 Persistent Zones
	•	Zones are saved to disk (NBT)
	•	Automatically restored on server restart
	•	Includes:
	•	Anchor positions
	•	Owner
	•	Zone name

⸻

👤 Ownership & Naming
	•	Zones track the player who created them
		•	(Optional) Support for naming via Name Tags

    ⸻

    📦 Installation

    Requirements
    	•	Minecraft 1.21.x (Fabric)
    	•	Fabric Loader 0.16+
    	•	Fabric API

    Steps
    	1.	Install Fabric Loader
    	2.	Install Fabric API
    	3.	Drop the GlowField .jar into your /mods folder
    	4.	Start the server

    ⸻

    ⚙️ Configuration

    Config file is generated at: `/config/glowfield.json`

    Example

```json
{
  "particlesEnabled": true,
  "damagePlayers": false,
  "pvpEnabled": false,
  "suppressMobSpawns": true,
  "damageMobs": true,
  "nameTagNamingEnabled": true,
  "allowNonMemberPlayerDamage": true,
  "persistCachedBounds": true,
  "renderVerticalParticleEdges": true,
  "renderTopParticleFace": false,
  "renderBottomParticleFace": false,
  "renderParticlesDownToGround": true,
  "renderParticlesForPartialState": true,
  "renderParticlesForForceFieldState": true,
  "renderParticlesForDegradingState": true,
  "forceFieldMinCharge": 4,
  "partialMinCharge": 1,
  "degradeEveryMobInteractions": 50,
  "degradingStateThreshold": 25,
  "hostileFieldPlayerDeathLimit": 5,
  "anchorBreakHitsRequired": 20,
  "particleIntervalTicks": 20,
  "entitySweepIntervalTicks": 10,
  "saveFlushIntervalTicks": 200,
  "particleRenderHeightBlocks": 1,
  "partialFieldDurationTicks": 240000,
  "forceFieldDurationTicks": 120000,
  "hostileForceFieldDurationTicks": 48000,
  "hostileFieldDamageIntervalTicks": 20,
  "forceFieldDamage": 4.0,
  "hostileFieldDamage": 4.0,
  "backlashDamage": 4.0,
  "backlashKnockback": 1.0,
  "anchorDestroyedExplosionPower": 0.0,
  "particleStep": 1.5,
  "particleViewPadding": 32.0,
  "hostileFieldActivationItem": "minecraft:echo_shard",
  "hostileFieldParticle": "minecraft:soul_fire_flame",
  "hitDecayEnabled": false,
  "anchorDestroyedExplosionCreatesFire": false,
  "hitDecayTimeTicks": 200,
  "backlashSlownessTicks": 60,
  "backlashSlownessAmplifier": 1,
  "backlashWitherTicks": 0,
  "backlashWitherAmplifier": 0,
  "stateParticles": {
    "degrading": "minecraft:ash",
    "inactive": "minecraft:end_rod",
    "force_field": "minecraft:portal",
    "partial": "minecraft:flash"
  }
}
```

    What each setting means
    	•	`particlesEnabled` — master switch for all zone particle rendering.
    	•	`damagePlayers` — if `true`, players inside a force-field-state zone take periodic magic damage during entity sweeps.
    	•	`pvpEnabled` — if `false`, player-vs-player damage is blocked when either the attacker or target is inside any zone.
    	•	`suppressMobSpawns` — if `true`, mob spawning is denied inside active zones (partial, degrading, or force field).
    	•	`damageMobs` — if `true`, mobs entering a force-field-state zone are killed by the zone during entity sweeps.
    	•	`nameTagNamingEnabled` — allows a player to rename their own zone by using a named Name Tag on one of that zone’s anchors.
    	•	`allowNonMemberPlayerDamage` — enables the hostile-zone mode that damages players who are neither the owner nor a member.
    	•	`persistCachedBounds` — currently unused by the code. It is saved in the config but does not change runtime behavior at the moment.
    	•	`renderVerticalParticleEdges` — renders particle columns around the zone perimeter.
    	•	`renderTopParticleFace` — renders a particle surface across the top face of the particle box.
    	•	`renderBottomParticleFace` — renders a particle surface across the bottom face of the particle box.
    	•	`renderParticlesDownToGround` — extends perimeter particle columns downward to the terrain instead of starting exactly at anchor height.
    	•	`renderParticlesForPartialState` — enables particles when a zone is in partial state.
    	•	`renderParticlesForForceFieldState` — enables particles when a zone is in full force-field state.
    	•	`renderParticlesForDegradingState` — enables particles when a zone is in degrading state.
    	•	`forceFieldMinCharge` — minimum anchor charge required for a zone to enter `force_field` state.
    	•	`partialMinCharge` — minimum anchor charge required for a zone to be active at all. If any anchor is below this value, the zone is inactive.
    	•	`degradeEveryMobInteractions` — number of counted zone interactions before every anchor loses 1 charge.
    	•	`degradingStateThreshold` — interaction progress value at which an active zone switches from normal behavior to the `degrading` visual state.
    	•	`hostileFieldPlayerDeathLimit` — how many player deaths a hostile zone can inflict before the field collapses and becomes inactive until recharge.
    	•	`anchorBreakHitsRequired` — how many outsider break attempts a hostile anchor can absorb before the next attempt is allowed to destroy it. Default is `20`.
    	•	`particleIntervalTicks` — how often particles are rendered. `20` ticks is about once per second.
    	•	`entitySweepIntervalTicks` — how often entities inside loaded zones are checked for damage effects.
    	•	`saveFlushIntervalTicks` — how often dirty zone data is flushed to disk automatically.
    	•	`particleRenderHeightBlocks` — height of the particle box above the anchor Y level. `1` renders a single-block-tall band.
    	•	`partialFieldDurationTicks` — maximum lifetime of the weaker spawn-prevention field before recharge is needed. Default is 10 Minecraft days.
    	•	`forceFieldDurationTicks` — maximum lifetime of a standard force field before recharge is needed. Default is 5 Minecraft days.
    	•	`hostileForceFieldDurationTicks` — maximum lifetime of the hostile player-damaging force field before recharge is needed. Default is 2 Minecraft days.
    	•	`forceFieldDamage` — amount of player damage per sweep when `damagePlayers` is enabled. This is separate from hostile-zone outsider damage.
    	•	`hostileFieldDamageIntervalTicks` — how often a hostile zone damages non-members standing inside it.
    	•	`hostileFieldDamage` — damage dealt each hostile-zone damage tick to a non-owner, non-member player inside the zone.
    	•	`backlashDamage` — magic damage dealt to outsiders when they try to break an anchor in a hostile zone.
    	•	`backlashKnockback` — knockback strength applied to outsiders when they try to break an anchor in a hostile zone.
    	•	`anchorDestroyedExplosionPower` — explosion power applied when an anchor is actually destroyed. Set to `0.0` to disable explosions.
    	•	`particleStep` — spacing between particle samples. Lower values create denser walls but cost more packets.
    	•	`particleViewPadding` — currently present in config, but not used by the current rendering code.
    	•	`hostileFieldActivationItem` — item consumed on each anchor interaction while attuning a fully charged zone into hostile mode.
    	•	`hostileFieldParticle` — particle used while a hostile non-member-damaging zone is active.
    	•	`anchorDestroyedExplosionCreatesFire` — if `true`, anchor-destruction explosions can create fire.
    	•	`hitDecayEnabled` — if `true`, anchor break progress from outsiders decays over time instead of accumulating forever.
    	•	`hitDecayTimeTicks` — decay interval used when `hitDecayEnabled` is on. Every interval removes 1 stored hit from an anchor.
    	•	`backlashSlownessTicks` / `backlashSlownessAmplifier` — optional slowness effect applied during anchor backlash. Set duration to `0` to disable.
    	•	`backlashWitherTicks` / `backlashWitherAmplifier` — optional wither effect applied during anchor backlash. Set duration to `0` to disable.
    	•	`stateParticles.inactive` — particle id reserved for inactive zones. Inactive zones currently do not render particles, so this is effectively unused unless rendering logic changes.
    	•	`stateParticles.partial` — particle id used for partial-state zones.
    	•	`stateParticles.force_field` — particle id used for force-field-state zones.
    	•	`stateParticles.degrading` — particle id used for degrading-state zones.

    Zone states
    	•	`inactive` — any anchor is below `partialMinCharge`; no protection effects run.
    	•	`partial` — all anchors meet `partialMinCharge`, but the zone has not reached full force-field charge.
    	•	`force_field` — all anchors meet `forceFieldMinCharge`; this is the state that damages mobs and can optionally damage non-members if the hostile mode has been attuned.
    	•	`degrading` — interaction progress has reached `degradingStateThreshold` and the zone still has charge remaining. This is a warning state before the next charge loss event.

    ⸻

    🧱 How to Use
    	1.	Place 4 Respawn Anchors in a rectangle (corners)
    	2.	Charge them using Glowstone
    	3.	Ensure all anchors meet charge requirements
    	4.	Zone activates automatically

    Hostile Player-Damaging Mode
    	1.	Stand inside your own fully charged zone
    	2.	Use the configured activation item on each of the 4 anchors
    	3.	Each anchor interaction consumes 1 item
    	4.	After all 4 anchors are attuned, the zone damages players who are not the owner and not zone members
    	5.	Use `/glowfield member add <player>` and `/glowfield member remove <player>` while standing in your zone to manage safe players
    	6.	Outsiders cannot break hostile anchors instantly. Their break attempts are canceled, backlash is applied, and the anchor only breaks after enough accumulated hits
